{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-14625/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-14625"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:46:25"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man glares at people behind him."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-14625","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-14625"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1/8e1a01b0-f553-4cab-9ccb-f0799eb4107d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-02T19:56:55.728Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Given Alma’s foreign background and Reynolds’s repeated emphasis on “Englishness” (his breakfast, the flag on his house, etc.), <em>Phantom Thread</em> may be read as an allegory of the clash between the English and the foreign/other European. Reynolds struggles to understand Alma’s lust for life and wishes to remain in his closed-off, stately English existence. The New Year’s Eve ball, then, presents this clash in carnivalesque form with vibrant costumes, wild music, and drunken escapades.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14625/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:36.268411624203765,55.26025079617824,332.3273288216561,214.18889331210187"}}}]}]}]}